Question 22.Question: How long would it take to deposit 0.08g of copper from CuCl2 solution by passing current of 0.5A? [Cu = 64, F = 96,500 C mol-1]
Question 22.Explanation:
Using Faraday's first law of electrolysis

Cu2+ + 2e- à Cu

From the equation above,

2 faradays will deposit 64g of Cu

Recall 1 faraday = 96,500C

Therefore, 2 faradays = 2 x 96,500C = 193,000C

It implies that 193,000C will deposit 64g

193,000C à 64g

X à 0.08g

X = (193000 × 0.08)/64

X = 241.25C

Recall Q = It

t = Q/I

t = 241.25/0.5

t = 482.5s

= 8.04 minutes
